\ symbol literals (:foo) intern on use; string>symbol interns at runtime.

\ a literal equals itself
:foo :foo = .                      \ -1

\ distinct names are distinct
:foo :bar = .                      \ 0

\ :foo and a symbol defined via `symbol` share identity
symbol baz
baz :baz = .                       \ -1

\ string>symbol matches the same-named literal
"hello" string>symbol :hello = .   \ -1

\ a colon-prefixed token that names a defined word still resolves as the word
\ (here :foo is only ever a symbol; words like :] are unaffected)

\ symbols print as their name
:cat .                             \ cat

\ symbols live in sets without collapsing distinct names
:a :b :c 3 set size .       \ 3

\ duplicate symbols dedup in a set
:a :a :a 3 set size .       \ 1

\ two symbols made with `symbol` are distinct; same name interns equal
symbol one   symbol two
one two = .                        \ 0
one :one = .                       \ 1
